    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so basically they just want to follow exactly what was written back then to keep things consistent. but isn't there a lot of criticism that it's kind of just a way for judges to push a specific political agenda under the guise of being 'neutral'? i've heard people say it's more about ideology than actual law.",
