    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so that's the view from the critics. but if you look at the proponents' side, isn't there a legitimate scholarly argument that it's the only way to prevent the constitution from becoming whatever a judge wants it to be? like, is it actually a valid legal framework or is the critique that it's just a mask pretty much the consensus among legal scholars?",
